    excerpt: 'The Doctor Who 50th Anniversary Doodle is a multi-level adventure game released on November 23, 2013, celebrating 50 years of the legendary BBC science fiction ...',
    content: `<p>The Doctor Who 50th Anniversary Doodle is a multi-level adventure game released on November 23, 2013, celebrating 50 years of the legendary BBC science fiction series. Nicknamed the &#8220;Whodle&#8221; by the team at Google, it&#8217;s one of the largest and most ambitious Doodles ever created — a full 8-bit style game where you play as any of the first eleven Doctors to recover the stolen Google letters from across time and space.</p>

<p>The premise is pure Doctor Who: those dastardly Daleks have stolen the letters G-O-O-G-L-E and scattered them throughout the universe. You pick your favourite Doctor (from William Hartnell&#8217;s First Doctor all the way to Matt Smith&#8217;s Eleventh) and pilot the TARDIS through six levels packed with iconic enemies. The game features Daleks shouting &#8220;EXTERMINATE!&#8221;, Cybermen declaring &#8220;You will be deleted!&#8221;, and the terrifying Weeping Angels who move impossibly fast when you&#8217;re not looking.</p>

<p>The Doodle was created by Matthew Cruickshank and a small team of Google engineers, with the BBC providing authentic sound effects from the show. What started as a request from a massive Doctor Who fan at Google became a months-long project. The BBC initially expected a simple animated doodle, but the team pushed for something more ambitious — a multi-level platform game that captured the spirit of time travel and adventure.</p>

<p>Each level represents a different era. You&#8217;ll navigate an industrial Dalek base, leap across moving platforms in prehistoric times while avoiding a pterodactyl, sneak past Cybermen near Tower Bridge in London, survive a rainy graveyard where a Weeping Angel hunts you, and finally navigate a spaceship with deadly electrified floor panels. If you get caught, your Doctor regenerates into the next incarnation (with a time penalty), cycling through all eleven faces.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How To Play Doctor Who 50th Anniversary</strong></h2>

<p>Click the play button and choose your favourite Doctor from the selection screen showing all eleven incarnations.</p>

<p>Use arrow keys or click on tiles to move the Doctor around each level. You can click multiple spaces ahead rather than moving one square at a time.</p>

<p>Flip switches to activate platforms, lower bridges, and open pathways. Each level requires solving simple puzzles while avoiding patrolling enemies.</p>

<p>Collect the letter in each level, then return safely to the TARDIS to travel to the next adventure.</p>

<p>Watch out for Weeping Angels in the graveyard — keep moving or they&#8217;ll corner you. In the final level, carefully time your movements through the electrified floor grid to avoid instant death.</p>
<div class='code-block code-block-1' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'>

</div>
<!-- CONTENT END 1 -->`,
